Cape Town The quick response by members of the Somerset West police has led to arrest of three men who attempted an armed robbery at a fast food outlet at a mall in Somerset West, Cape Town, early on Sunday morning, Western Cape police said. Police were alerted to a robbery in progress at the establishment at 6.15am and reacted swiftly, Lt-Col Andr&egrave; Traut said. &quot;Upon their arrival on the scene, four suspects made an attempt to flee. Police managed to apprehend three of the four, aged 32, 41, and 41, and confiscate two prohibited firearms. &quot;The fourth suspect evaded arrest and is being sought. The suspects, who are from Makhaza, Khayelitsha, are due in court once they have been charged,&quot; Traut said.&nbsp; African News Agency